org.openscience.cdk.qsar.model.R
Class CNNClassificationModelFit

java.lang.Object
  org.openscience.cdk.qsar.model.R.CNNClassificationModelFit
Deprecated. 

public class CNNClassificationModelFit
extends java.lang.Object

A class that wraps the return value from R function, nnet(). This is an internal class used by R to return the result of the call to nnet. As a result it should not be instantiated by the user. The actual modeling class, CNNClassificationModel, provides acess to the various fields of this object.

Author:
Rajarshi Guha
Requires:
r-project
Belongs to CDK module:
qsar

                                 double value,
                                 double[] hessian)
Deprecated. 
Constructs an object to contain a CNN classification fit. This class should not be instantiated directly and is only required withtin R

Parameters:
noutput - The number of output neurons (ie the number of predicted variables)
nobs - The number of observations
weights - A 1-dimensional array containing the weights and biases
fitted - A 1-dimensional array containing the fitted values
residual - A 1-dimensional array containing the residuals of the fitted values
value - The final value of the cost function
hessian - A 1-dimensional array containing the Hessian
